 there was a star. It was small, but in the sky. It did not shine very brightly, but it was very warm. It moved around a lot, but it stayed in one spot most of the time. This meant that a lot of other things got to live near it, and near its friends. Eventually, someone saw that this was a good thing, and everyone agreed that this was a good thing, so people kept doing it. They said 'Let there be light,'
